<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1378,1979]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1882,1907]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[332,624,1883,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ctenocolum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acapulcensis">
<emphasis box="[332,624,1883,1907]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Ctenocolum acapulcensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other species by having hind femur without toothed carina at the external ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[577,662,1918,1943]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 76" captionStartId="14.[151,263,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[216,1383,211,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[200,1387,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 76. Posterior leg, external view: 72 Ctenocolum punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 73 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 74 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro- Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 75 C. acapulcensis; 76 C. janzeni. Scale: 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286739/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[630,662,1918,1943]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="75.0">75</number>
</figureCitation>
). It is the only species of the group that has conspicuous teeth at the base of striae 
<number box="[306,320,1955,1979]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[374,391,1955,1979]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="4.0">4</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,151,1473]" box="[199,781,151,176]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,372,151,176]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Redescription.</emphasis>
BL: 
<quantity box="[430,568,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="4.6" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="4.4">4.4–4.8 mm</quantity>
; BW: 
<quantity box="[638,776,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="3.25" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Integument. Dorsum black, sometimes mostly black and reddish brown. Antenna brown and dark brown; first antennomeres 
<number box="[315,372,224,248]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10</number>
almost entirely dark brown, last antennomere brown (
<figureCitation box="[995,1080,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 21" captionStartId="5.[151,262,1469,1492]" captionTargetBox="[184,1433,256,1431]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1448]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 21. Dorsal habitus: 17 Ctenocolum triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 18 C. acapulcensis; 19 C. janzeni; 20 C. salvini (lectotype); 21 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698643" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698643/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[1049,1080,224,248]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pygidium rufous or brown or rufous and dark brown. Ventral region rufous, black and brown. Front and middle femur and tibia brown or brown and dark brown to black; hind femur reddish brown and black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Pubescence. Pronotum brown, yellowish gray and black; sparse setae exposing the integument forming an oval, wide area from anterior to posterior region divided or not by transversal and longitudinal strip of denser setae and on each lateral region one small rounded area (
<figureCitation box="[750,837,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 21" captionStartId="5.[151,262,1469,1492]" captionTargetBox="[184,1433,256,1431]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1448]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 21. Dorsal habitus: 17 Ctenocolum triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 18 C. acapulcensis; 19 C. janzeni; 20 C. salvini (lectotype); 21 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698643" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698643/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[806,837,404,428]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elytra strongly variegated, brown, yellowish gray, black and white setae; interstria 
<number box="[524,538,440,464]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
bellow scutellum with yellowish gray and white short dense strip; interstria 
<number box="[1422,1436,440,464]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
only with white setae at submedian region (
<figureCitation box="[653,739,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 21" captionStartId="5.[151,262,1469,1492]" captionTargetBox="[184,1433,256,1431]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1448]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 21. Dorsal habitus: 17 Ctenocolum triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 18 C. acapulcensis; 19 C. janzeni; 20 C. salvini (lectotype); 21 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698643" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698643/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[708,739,476,500]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pygidium dense, white and yellowish gray; sparse setae on two basal and four lateral small areas; at median region a larger area with sparse setae (
<figureCitation box="[1166,1253,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 35 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 35 – 43. Pygidium of male: 35 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 36 C. colburni; 37 C. martiale; 38 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 39 C. podagricus; 40 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 41 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 42 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 43 C. acapulcensis. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698649" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698649/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[1221,1253,512,536]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ventral region brown, yellowish gray and white (
<figureCitation box="[534,618,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 61 – 65" captionStartId="12.[151,263,1650,1673]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,261,1604]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1629]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 61 – 65. Lateral habitus: 61 Ctenocolum triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 62 C. acapulcensis; 63 C. janzeni; 64 C. salvini (lectotype); 65 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698657/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[586,618,548,573]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="62.0">62</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Head. Ocular sinus 
<quantity box="[422,512,584,608]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
; ocular index 8.0– 
<number box="[723,772,583,608]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="11.6">11.6</number>
; length of eyes in frontal view behind sinus 
<quantity box="[1275,1375,584,608]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.34">0.34 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1435,1458]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,176,1415]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,161,1416]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 34. Frontal habitus: 31 Ctenocolum acapulcensis; 32 C. janzeni; 33 C. salvini (lectotype); 34 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698647" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698647/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,182,620,644]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antenna strongly serrate from antennomere 
<number box="[697,711,620,644]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
or 
<quantity box="[749,829,620,645]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" metricValueMax="2.54" metricValueMin="1.016" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="in" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4-10 in</quantity>
male. Frons with frontal carina (
<figureCitation box="[1197,1281,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1435,1458]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,176,1415]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,161,1416]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 34. Frontal habitus: 31 Ctenocolum acapulcensis; 32 C. janzeni; 33 C. salvini (lectotype); 34 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698647" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698647/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[1250,1281,620,644]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Prothorax. Pronotum with median gibbosity strongly elevated, divided or not by longitudinal sulcus and divided by transversal sulcus (
<figureCitation box="[498,584,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 61 – 65" captionStartId="12.[151,263,1650,1673]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,261,1604]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1629]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 61 – 65. Lateral habitus: 61 Ctenocolum triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 62 C. acapulcensis; 63 C. janzeni; 64 C. salvini (lectotype); 65 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698657/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[552,584,692,717]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="62.0">62</number>
</figureCitation>
); lateral gibbosity strongly elevated; basal lobe with or without depression and slightly or strongly emarginated (
<figureCitation box="[572,655,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 21" captionStartId="5.[151,262,1469,1492]" captionTargetBox="[184,1433,256,1431]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1448]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 21. Dorsal habitus: 17 Ctenocolum triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 18 C. acapulcensis; 19 C. janzeni; 20 C. salvini (lectotype); 21 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698643" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698643/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[624,655,728,752]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Mesothorax and metathorax. Elytra, striae with punctures moderately impressed; conspicuous teeth at base of striae 
<number box="[223,237,800,824]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[300,317,800,824]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="4.0">4</number>
; tooth of stria 
<number box="[496,510,800,824]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="4.0">4</number>
closer to base of tooth of stria 
<number box="[891,905,800,824]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
than to anterior margin of elytra; stria 
<number box="[1375,1389,799,824]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="6.0">6</number>
not impressed, formed only by isolated puntuation. 
<collectingCountry box="[697,753,836,861]" name="India" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur (
<figureCitation box="[847,930,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 76" captionStartId="14.[151,263,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[216,1383,211,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[200,1387,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 76. Posterior leg, external view: 72 Ctenocolum punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 73 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 74 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro- Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 75 C. acapulcensis; 76 C. janzeni. Scale: 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286739/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[901,930,836,861]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="75.0">75</number>
</figureCitation>
) on external ventral margin without toothed carina; without denticles above of external ventral margin; pecten with 
<number box="[970,1040,872,896]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
teeth. 
<collectingCountry box="[1119,1175,871,896]" name="India" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia (
<figureCitation box="[1252,1335,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 76" captionStartId="14.[151,263,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[216,1383,211,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[200,1387,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 76. Posterior leg, external view: 72 Ctenocolum punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 73 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 74 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro- Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 75 C. acapulcensis; 76 C. janzeni. Scale: 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286739/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[1306,1335,871,896]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="75.0">75</number>
</figureCitation>
) slightly emarginated beside mucro; lateral coronal denticles absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,151,1473]" box="[199,1406,943,968]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Abdomen. Pygidium subequal, oval, at median basal region with moderately impressed punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1309,1394,943,968]" captionStart="FIGURES 35 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 35 – 43. Pygidium of male: 35 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 36 C. colburni; 37 C. martiale; 38 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 39 C. podagricus; 40 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 41 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 42 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 43 C. acapulcensis. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698649" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698649/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[1362,1394,944,968]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Male genitalia. Median lobe with ventral valve as long as wide, lateral margin straight on subapical region (
<figureCitation box="[159,248,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 90" captionStartId="18.[151,263,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[202,1384,193,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[202,1385,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 90. Male genitalia, median lobe: 85 Ctenocolum pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 86 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 87 C. acapulcensis; 88 C. janzeni; 89 C. salvini (paralectotype); 90 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698661/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[217,248,1016,1040]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="87.0">87</number>
</figureCitation>
), basal margin not emarginated. Internal sac, lateral apex with short tuft of setae, hinge sclerite Sshaped, long, extending over 
<number box="[487,497,1052,1076]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[508,524,1052,1076]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
of subapical region; subapical region with homogeneously distributed spicules, forming an elongated strip; median region with homogeneously distributed spicules, dense denticles and smooth sclerite, subsquare with stems oriented forward, longer than central region (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1113,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 90" captionStartId="18.[151,263,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[202,1384,193,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[202,1385,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 90. Male genitalia, median lobe: 85 Ctenocolum pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 86 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 87 C. acapulcensis; 88 C. janzeni; 89 C. salvini (paralectotype); 90 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698661/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[1081,1113,1124,1148]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="87.0">87</number>
</figureCitation>
); submedian region without sclerite and denticles; basal region with spicules, without denticles and spines. Tegmen (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1273,1159,1184]" captionStart="FIGURES 91 – 99" captionStartId="19.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 91 – 99. Male genitalia, tegmen, lateral lobe: 91 C. aquilus (paratype); 92 C. colburni; 93 C. martiale (holotype); 94 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 95 C. podagricus; 96 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 97 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 98 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 99 C. acapulcensis. Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698663" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698663/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[1241,1273,1160,1184]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="99.0">99</number>
</figureCitation>
), lateral lobes separated by emargination about 
<number box="[535,571,1196,1221]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="0.5">0.5</number>
times the length of lateral lobes; internal margin near end of emargination curved, forming a &quot;U&quot;; not expanded at apex, about the same width of the median region; without membranous projection at apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Note. The males of this species are the only in the genus with strongly serrate antenna. Unfourtunately, we had not females in our samples to compare antennal forms.</paragraph>
